	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=7610><span id=Scholar>Quantli</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>26 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.06]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I played it differently from Aprry.<br><br>I dispensed with the combat spells (disempower and walking sleep) and just relied on DoT and Root until the mob was down to 20% health and was ready to run.<br><br>This technique reduced down time as you can med while killing the mob.<br><br>I found the melee debuffs had too many resists and caused too much downtime.<br><br>I normally pulled with the disease dot as this takes the longest to cast.<br><br>Kanix<br>Shaman with 39 Blessings of the Tribunal<br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
