	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=7610><span id=Scholar>Quantli</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>26 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.03]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The way I played at 17 is very different to the way I play now, largely because I was only wearing banded and my pet was 17 levels away.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>I found that, at 17, the mobs did too much damage when I meleed them and the debuffs were ineffective and unreliable.  These days I dot, debuff and melee,  in order to get the maximum effectiveness from my pet.<br><br>The great thing about shammies is that sometime you play a like a druid, a warrior or a cleric.  Why just limit yourself to one?<br><br>Kanix<br>Shaman with 39 Blessings of the Tribunal.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Sep  9 09:34:02 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
